1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,127
This demo uses an AI-generated narration voice.

2
00:00:03,127 --> 00:00:06,255
For many Deaf and hard-of-hearing people, a

3
00:00:06,255 --> 00:00:09,382
simple phone-only task can become a barrier.

4
00:00:09,382 --> 00:00:13,850
SayAhead lets the user read, guide, and control the conversation.

5
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:16,880
It is a supervised, text-first calling assistant.

6
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:19,909
The user sets the destination, goal, facts

7
00:00:19,909 --> 00:00:22,939
that may be shared, and hard boundaries.

8
00:00:22,939 --> 00:00:27,700
The assistant handles the conversation, but the user keeps final control.

9
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:31,519
Here, Maya wants to reserve a quiet library room.

10
00:00:31,519 --> 00:00:35,337
She approves only the minimum facts the assistant needs

11
00:00:35,337 --> 00:00:38,731
and forbids fees, payments, or new personal details.

12
00:00:38,731 --> 00:00:42,550
She confirms that this is a user-initiated, low-risk call.

13
00:00:42,550 --> 00:00:48,171
For reliable public judging, this site deliberately simulates the GPT-5.6 planning

14
00:00:48,171 --> 00:00:53,280
stages and uses the same structured contract without external credentials.

15
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:58,390
In configured mode, the OpenAI Responses API uses GPT-5.6 Sol

16
00:00:58,390 --> 00:01:03,500
to turn approved facts and boundaries into a reviewable plan.

17
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,392
Nothing happens before review.

18
00:01:05,392 --> 00:01:08,703
Maya can check the objective, conversation path,

19
00:01:08,703 --> 00:01:11,541
success criteria, and every approval gate.

20
00:01:11,541 --> 00:01:16,270
The opening identifies SayAhead’s AI accessibility assistant and asks affirmative

21
00:01:16,270 --> 00:01:21,000
consent to continue with live transcription and temporary text review.

22
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,991
What you are about to see is a public demo simulation;

23
00:01:24,991 --> 00:01:27,531
it does not place a phone call.

24
00:01:27,531 --> 00:01:30,797
The Twilio and OpenAI Realtime path is implemented and

25
00:01:30,797 --> 00:01:33,700
has been tested with a consented, allowlisted destination.

26
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:37,413
Rather than pressure the person answering with a checklist, the

27
00:01:37,413 --> 00:01:41,125
assistant explains that it is helping someone use live captions,

28
00:01:41,125 --> 00:01:44,838
asks one warm consent question, and then uses the plan

29
00:01:44,838 --> 00:01:48,550
to make reasonable low-risk choices while keeping the exchange natural.

30
00:01:48,550 --> 00:01:52,375
Maya can pause without speaking, type what SayAhead should

31
00:01:52,375 --> 00:01:56,200
say, correct a detail, resume, or end the call.

32
00:01:56,200 --> 00:02:00,450
Large two-speaker captions clearly separate the person answering from the

33
00:02:00,450 --> 00:02:04,700
assistant, so she can follow the conversation at a glance.

34
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:08,803
When the library offers the room, the assistant stops.

35
00:02:08,803 --> 00:02:11,538
Nothing is committed until Maya chooses.

36
00:02:11,538 --> 00:02:17,009
Payments, emergencies, marketing, and high-stakes medical or financial calls are blocked entirely;

37
00:02:17,009 --> 00:02:20,200
this first release stays deliberately low risk.

38
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:24,340
After the call, Maya gets confirmed details, the reference

39
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:28,480
number, next actions, and the full conversation for review.

40
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:31,700
In configured mode, GPT-5.6 structures this outcome.

41
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:34,920
SayAhead does not record or store audio;

42
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:38,140
the text remains only in this browser

43
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:40,900
tab and can be cleared explicitly.

44
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:46,275
Codex helped me implement and test the accessible React interface,

45
00:02:46,275 --> 00:02:51,112
safety guardrails, GPT-5.6 integration, and the Twilio-to-OpenAI Realtime bridge.

46
00:02:51,112 --> 00:02:54,875
SayAhead turns phone calls into conversations the

47
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:58,100
user can read, guide, and control.
